<P>TWO SERMONS Preached at <HI>New-Brun&s;wick,</HI> In the Year 1741. ON The <HI>Prie&s;tly Office</HI> of <HI>Christ.</HI> AND The Virtue of <HI>Charity.</HI></P>
<P>By <HI>Gilbert Tennent,</HI> A. M. And Mini&s;ter of the Go&s;pel there.</P>
<Q><BIBL><HI>Heb. 4.15.</HI></BIBL>
<P>For we have not an High Prie&s;t which cannot be touched with the feeling of our Infirmities; but was in all Points tempted like as we are, yet without Sin.</P>
<BIBL><HI>Heb. 13.1.</HI></BIBL>
<P>Let brotherly Love continue.</P></Q>
<P><HI>BOSTON: N. E.</HI> Printed and Sold by S. KNEELAND and T. GREEN, in Queen&s;treet over again&s;t the Pri&s;on. 1742.</P>
